The paper proposes a method for improving recommendation performance using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks for feature learning and interaction modeling suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories. Finally, the evaluation of scalability and sensitivity suggests a potential fit for the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
